12/08/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A total of 200 Croatian troops are in Afghanistan now, serving with the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan peace mission following a rotation Friday (August 10th).
The new brigade will be deployed for six months.
Also on Friday, Slovenia rotated new brigades of soldiers into Kosovo and Afghanistan.
They are serving within the crisis reaction forces there.
(Javno.com, Dnevnik, A1, SRNA, RTRS - 10/08/07)
